The paper deals with zero-shot learning, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The proposed method involves propagating attribute annotations using sparse coding, which is a technique commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of web images returned by image search engines, which falls under multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
